# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# deploy/stacks/secrets.example — B3 Docker-secret inventory for skchat-stack.yml
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# This file documents the FIVE Docker secrets that skchat-stack.yml consumes and
# is ALSO the template for the gitignored env file that make-secrets.sh reads.
#
#   1. Copy to the (gitignored) secret env file:
#         cp deploy/stacks/secrets.example deploy/stacks/.env.secrets
#   2. Fill in every value below in .env.secrets.
#   3. chmod 600 deploy/stacks/.env.secrets
#   4. Run:  deploy/stacks/make-secrets.sh
#         → creates each value as a `docker secret` (Swarm raft, encrypted at rest)
#   5. NEVER commit .env.secrets (it is in .gitignore).
#
# Each VAR below maps to a Docker secret NAME (external: true in the stack) and
# is mounted at /run/secrets/<name>, read by the service via a *_FILE env var.
#
#   env var (here)            docker secret name        consumed by (service / *_FILE env)
#   ────────────────────────  ────────────────────────  ──────────────────────────────────
#   LIVEKIT_API_KEY           livekit_api_key           sk-access  SKCHAT_LIVEKIT_API_KEY_FILE
#   LIVEKIT_API_SECRET        livekit_api_secret        sk-access  SKCHAT_LIVEKIT_API_SECRET_FILE
#   TURN_SECRET               turn_secret               sk-access  SKCHAT_TURN_SECRET_FILE
#   SKMEMORY_PG_PASSWORD      skmemory_pg_password      daemon + skcomms-api  SKMEMORY_PG_PASSWORD_FILE
#   VOICE_FALLBACK_URL        voice_fallback_url        voice      SKVOICE_FALLBACK_URL_FILE
#
# ── B4 alignment (MUST match) ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
#   livekit_api_key   + livekit_api_secret  →  MUST equal the two halves of B4's
#       LIVEKIT_KEYS ("apiKey: apiSecret" in /var/data/deploy_livekit/livekit.env).
#       skchat MINTS LiveKit JWTs with these; LiveKit verifies with the same pair.
#   turn_secret  →  MUST equal B4 coturn's SKCHAT_TURN_SECRET
#       (--static-auth-secret in coturn-stack.yml / /var/data/deploy_coturn/coturn.env).
#       skchat derives short-lived HMAC TURN creds from it; coturn validates them.
#
# ── OpenBao mapping (long-term; see deploy/SECRETS.md §3) ──────────────────────
#   livekit_api_key       secret/data/skchat/prod/livekit_api_key
#   livekit_api_secret    secret/data/skchat/prod/livekit_api_secret
#   turn_secret           secret/data/skchat/prod/turn_secret
#   skmemory_pg_password  secret/data/skchat/prod/pg_password
#   voice_fallback_url    secret/data/skchat/prod/voice_fallback_url
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ─── LiveKit SFU JWT signer (P0) ───────────────────────────────────────────────
# The key half + secret half of B4's LIVEKIT_KEYS.  Generate (B4 side of truth):
#   livekit-cli generate-keys      # prints API_KEY + API_SECRET
# or:  KEY=$(openssl rand -hex 16); SECRET=$(openssl rand -hex 32)
LIVEKIT_API_KEY=
LIVEKIT_API_SECRET=

# ─── coturn TURN static secret (P0) ────────────────────────────────────────────
# MUST equal B4 coturn --static-auth-secret.  Generate once (shared with B4):
#   openssl rand -hex 32
TURN_SECRET=

# ─── skmem-pg Postgres password (P0) ───────────────────────────────────────────
SKMEMORY_PG_PASSWORD=

# ─── Fallback LLM endpoint (P1; may embed an auth token in the URL) ─────────────
# Full URL of the fallback voice LLM (e.g. http://user:token@host:port/v1/...).
# Treated as a secret because the token rides in the URL.
VOICE_FALLBACK_URL=
